{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648380","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648380"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:53:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:53:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18309"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18309","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18309"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11027"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78526"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11027","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11027"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18309"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63867"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25591"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25594"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26902"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78526"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA number of soft tissues structures are attached to the ischial tuberosity.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscles is attached to this site?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adductors","Hamstrings","Gluteus maximus","Iliopsoas","Quadriceps"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eischial tuberosity\u003C/strong\u003E is a bony prominence located on the inferior part of the pelvis. It serves as the attachment site for the hamstring muscles, which include the biceps femoris, semitendinosus, and semimembranosus. These muscles are responsible for knee flexion and hip extension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Equadriceps muscles\u003C/strong\u003E attach to the patella and tibial tuberosity, not the ischial tuberosity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egluteus maximus muscle\u003C/strong\u003E attaches to the iliotibial tract and the gluteal tuberosity of the femur, not the ischial tuberosity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eiliopsoas muscle\u003C/strong\u003E attaches to the lesser trochanter of the femur, not the ischial tuberosity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eadductor muscles\u003C/strong\u003E primarily attach to the pubis and the linea aspera of the femur, not the ischial tuberosity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The ischial tuberosity serves as the attachment site for the hamstring muscles.","The ischial tuberosity is involved in weight-bearing when sitting."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"it